I should preface this review by saying I'm way into pizza.  Walking into the place, I think it definitely reminds me of home. Really nice smell to it, baked goods, everything seemed fresh. This is family run and owned, you can tell.  I ordered a half Sicilian with bacon online with an order of fries. They had it ready when I got there in like 25 minutes. Friendly enough staff, speaking Spanish. If you, like many of these other reviewers, can't stand hearing another language in Waltham of all places, maybe don't go to a restaurant that specializes in ethnic food. They clearly speak and understand English, too. Service could not be more professional on that front.  The food is pretty good. The pizza is tasty. The bacon was really nice and genuine. They gave me a whole lot of pizza. Not so much sauce which is how I prefer it, a little more cheese than average, and a pretty thick crust. Not everyone's style but the pizza definitely catered to my tastes. Solid 8/10, would absolutely order again.  Fries were pretty standard pizza joint fries, a little crisper than average of anything. Also tasty.  Whole visit was enjoyable and I'm going to order again for sure. Very affordable pricing.  Definitely continue to support small places like this in Waltham. Moody Street is one of the best places to come to eat because of this.
